n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949, referred to in subsec. (b)(1), (4), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-30/ch288"},"text":"act June 30, 1949, ch. 288","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/377"},"text":"63 Stat. 377","children":[],"tail":", which was substantially repealed and restated in this chapter, chapters 3 to 11 of this title, and division C (except sections 3302, 3307(e), 3501(b), 3509, 3906, 4710, and 4711) of subtitle I of Title 41, Public Contracts, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1, 6(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1062"},"text":"116 Stat. 1062","children":[],"tail":", 1304, which Act enacted this title, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3, 7(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3677"},"text":"124 Stat. 3677","children":[],"tail":", 3855, which Act enacted Title 41. Provisions of former title I of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1949","children":[],"tail":", now appear in chapter 3 of this title relating to organization of General Services Administration. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 1949 Act note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 41","children":[],"tail":" and Tables. For disposition of sections of former Title 40, Public Buildings, Property, and Works, and former Title 41, Public Contracts, see Disposition Tables preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 41","children":[],"tail":", respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Surplus Property Act of 1944, referred to in subsec. (b)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-10-03/ch479"},"text":"act Oct. 3, 1944, ch. 479","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/765"},"text":"58 Stat. 765","children":[],"tail":", which was classified principally to sections 1611 to 1646 of the former Appendix to Title 50, War and National Defense, and was repealed effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1949","children":[],"tail":", with the exception of sections 1622, 1631, 1637, and 1641 of the former Appendix to Title 50, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-30/ch288/tVI/s602/a/1"},"text":"act June 30, 1949, ch. 288, title VI, § 602(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/399"},"text":"63 Stat. 399","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-05/ch849/s6/a"},"text":"Sept. 5, 1950, ch. 849, § 6(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/583"},"text":"64 Stat. 583","children":[],"tail":". Sections 1622 and 1641 were partially repealed by the 1949 act, and section 1622 was editorially reclassified and is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s545"},"text":"section 545 of Title 40","children":[],"tail":", Public Buildings, Property, and Works. Section 1622(g) was repealed and reenacted as sections 47151 to 47153 of Title 49, Transportation, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1(e), 7(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1278-1280"},"text":"108 Stat. 1278–1280","children":[],"tail":", 1379. Section 1631 was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-06-07/ch190/s6/e"},"text":"act June 7, 1939, ch. 190, § 6(e)","children":[],"tail":", as added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-23/ch590"},"text":"act July 23, 1946, ch. 590","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/599"},"text":"60 Stat. 599","children":[],"tail":", and is covered by sections 98 et seq. of Title 50. Section 1637 was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645/s21"},"text":"act June 25, 1948, ch. 645, § 21","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/862"},"text":"62 Stat. 862","children":[],"tail":", eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":", and is covered by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3287"},"text":"section 3287 of Title 18","children":[],"tail":", Crimes and Criminal Procedure. Provisions of section 1641 not repealed by the 1949 act were repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/256/s111/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–256, § 111(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-21"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/538"},"text":"75 Stat. 538","children":[],"tail":", and are covered by chapter 33 (§ 2451 et seq.) of Title 22, Foreign Relations and Intercourse. The provisions of the Surplus Property Act of 1944 originally repealed by the 1949 act are covered by provisions of the 1949 act which were classified to chapter 10 (§ 471 et seq.) of former Title 40, Public Buildings, Property, and Works, and which were repealed and reenacted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1, 6(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1062"},"text":"116 Stat. 1062","children":[],"tail":", 1304, as chapters 1 to 11 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
